WEBVTT

00:00:07.716 --> 00:00:08.483
- Get out of here!

00:00:08.517 --> 00:00:11.155
You can't make me
give you the key!

00:00:11.189 --> 00:00:12.190
And even if you did,

00:00:12.224 --> 00:00:13.828
I wouldn't show you
how to use it!

00:00:13.861 --> 00:00:18.269
<i>- What's going on? Are they
fighting about something?</i>

00:00:19.072 --> 00:00:20.374
<i>What should I do?</i>

00:00:20.407 --> 00:00:22.345
<i>It'd be rude to eavesdrop.</i>

00:00:22.378 --> 00:00:23.915
<i>But if they are fighting,</i>

00:00:23.948 --> 00:00:25.985
<i>I should try to help,
shouldn't I?</i>

00:00:26.018 --> 00:00:27.355
- [yelps]

00:00:27.388 --> 00:00:28.558
[groans]

00:00:28.591 --> 00:00:29.826
- [gasps]

00:00:29.860 --> 00:00:31.630
- [groans]

00:00:31.664 --> 00:00:33.166
- Stop it!

00:00:34.068 --> 00:00:36.573
What are you doing?!
Let him go!

00:00:37.408 --> 00:00:39.579
- There's no need
to be so noisy.

00:00:40.515 --> 00:00:41.416
Who are you?

00:00:41.449 --> 00:00:43.754
- How could you
treat a kid like that?!

00:00:43.788 --> 00:00:45.323
You should--[gasps]

00:00:45.357 --> 00:00:48.096
<i>He's not even budging...</i>

00:00:49.098 --> 00:00:50.400
<i>even though
he's got thinner arms</i>

00:00:50.433 --> 00:00:52.337
<i>and a smaller body than me.</i>

00:00:53.139 --> 00:00:55.645
- You take your hands off of me.

00:00:55.678 --> 00:00:57.180
- [gags]

00:00:58.350 --> 00:01:00.387
- You're weaker than I thought.

00:01:00.421 --> 00:01:02.725
I'm surprised
you got into the Corps.

00:01:03.862 --> 00:01:04.863
Huh?

00:01:05.865 --> 00:01:07.034
That box...

00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:08.303
I can sense something's in it.

00:01:08.336 --> 00:01:10.473
- [coughing]
- A demon, perhaps?

00:01:11.677 --> 00:01:14.315
- What are you hiding in there?
Show me.

00:01:14.348 --> 00:01:15.117
[gasps]

00:01:15.150 --> 00:01:17.789
- Stay back!

00:01:17.822 --> 00:01:19.827
<i>["Kizuna no Kiseki" playing]</i>

00:01:19.860 --> 00:01:26.873
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:49.873 --> 00:02:52.845
<i>[singers vocalizing]</i>

00:02:55.885 --> 00:02:57.287
- Huh.

00:02:58.090 --> 00:02:59.391
Eh?

00:03:02.130 --> 00:03:03.333
<i>He snatched him.</i>

00:03:03.367 --> 00:03:04.335
- Are you all right?

00:03:04.369 --> 00:03:05.738
- [groans] I'm fine!

00:03:05.772 --> 00:03:08.677
- You must be dizzy, though.
That's dangerous!

00:03:08.710 --> 00:03:09.979
- Get off me!

00:03:10.013 --> 00:03:13.286
I--I'm not giving the key
to anyone!

00:03:13.319 --> 00:03:15.257
Not even if you torture me!

00:03:15.290 --> 00:03:17.596
If I do, you'll only break it!

00:03:17.629 --> 00:03:20.234
- Have you been
through torture training?

00:03:20.267 --> 00:03:21.603
[both gasp]

00:03:21.637 --> 00:03:25.010
- Even most grownups aren't
able to endure through it.

00:03:25.043 --> 00:03:26.747
You would never last.

00:03:26.780 --> 00:03:29.586
And for your age,
you're exceedingly stupid.

00:03:30.755 --> 00:03:33.761
So what if it breaks?
Make another one.

00:03:34.563 --> 00:03:36.399
I'm curious. How many people

00:03:36.432 --> 00:03:38.670
do you think will perish
in the time you've wasted

00:03:38.704 --> 00:03:40.909
rambling about
a bunch of nonsense?

00:03:40.942 --> 00:03:42.411
[both gasp]

00:03:42.444 --> 00:03:46.520
- That's what it means to keep
a Hashira away from duty.

00:03:46.553 --> 00:03:47.822
Whether you like it or not,

00:03:47.856 --> 00:03:51.096
a Hashira's time
is worth far more than yours.

00:03:51.129 --> 00:03:54.101
If you don't understand,
I'll spell it out.

00:03:54.135 --> 00:03:56.272
Swordsmiths
aren't able to fight.

00:03:56.305 --> 00:03:58.243
You aren't able to save lives.

00:03:58.277 --> 00:04:00.180
Making weapons
is all you're good for.

00:04:00.213 --> 00:04:02.685
- [shuddering]

00:04:02.719 --> 00:04:04.823
- Now then, the key.

00:04:04.856 --> 00:04:08.530
You should know your place
in life and act accordingly.

00:04:08.564 --> 00:04:10.734
You're not a baby anymore.

00:04:12.805 --> 00:04:13.841
- [gasps]

00:04:14.843 --> 00:04:16.547
- What are you doing?

00:04:16.580 --> 00:04:19.118
- I just--
I don't know why, but...

00:04:19.151 --> 00:04:20.621
I can't stand you!

00:04:20.655 --> 00:04:22.725
What gives?!
Why be so cruel?!

00:04:22.759 --> 00:04:25.397
You have no right
to talk to a kid like that!

00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:28.570
- You think I'm being cruel?
Really?

00:04:28.604 --> 00:04:31.676
- Yes, I do! Even though
most of what you said

00:04:31.710 --> 00:04:35.417
is probably right and he
can't fight like a Hashira,

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:39.726
swordsmiths are still vital,
and that's a fact!

00:04:42.064 --> 00:04:43.399
They might not fight,

00:04:43.433 --> 00:04:45.805
but the skills they have
are amazing!

00:04:45.839 --> 00:04:48.577
- Without them,
we wouldn't have any swords.

00:04:48.611 --> 00:04:51.348
It's thanks to them
that we can fight!

00:04:52.151 --> 00:04:54.221
It's true that they need us,

00:04:54.254 --> 00:04:56.527
but it's also true
that we need them!

00:04:56.560 --> 00:04:58.831
We're all fighting
the same battle here.

00:04:58.864 --> 00:05:00.835
Day in and day out,
each in our own way--

00:05:00.868 --> 00:05:01.770
- Apologies...

00:05:02.806 --> 00:05:05.711
but I don't have time
to waste on your speech.

00:05:05.745 --> 00:05:06.747
You understand.

00:05:06.780 --> 00:05:08.015
- [gasps]

00:05:11.524 --> 00:05:12.692
BOY: What do we do?

00:05:12.725 --> 00:05:15.263
I don't know
if I carry him by myself.

00:05:15.297 --> 00:05:17.468
- No worries.
I'll carry him back.

00:05:17.502 --> 00:05:19.706
As long as he doesn't wake soon.

00:05:19.739 --> 00:05:20.975
[Tanjiro groans]

00:05:21.008 --> 00:05:22.210
- His eyelids are twitching,

00:05:22.244 --> 00:05:24.817
which means he's
gonna wake up any second!

00:05:24.850 --> 00:05:26.787
- See you!
- H--Hey!

00:05:26.820 --> 00:05:27.922
- [gasps]

00:05:27.956 --> 00:05:30.661
- Uh, are you okay?

00:05:30.694 --> 00:05:32.765
You shouldn't get up so fast.

00:05:32.799 --> 00:05:34.201
- Mr. Haganezuka!

00:05:34.234 --> 00:05:36.573
- Eh?
- Was he here just now?

00:05:36.606 --> 00:05:39.078
- No! I mean, why would he be?

00:05:39.111 --> 00:05:40.581
[hums a tune]

00:05:40.614 --> 00:05:43.554
- Really? Thought I heard him.

00:05:43.588 --> 00:05:45.658
[gasps] The Hashira!

00:05:45.692 --> 00:05:48.831
- I ended up giving him the key,
so he took off.

00:05:48.864 --> 00:05:51.102
- So you gave it to him?

00:05:51.135 --> 00:05:53.306
I guess
you didn't have a choice.

00:05:53.339 --> 00:05:56.179
Well, since I don't know
what's going on,

00:05:56.212 --> 00:05:58.216
I shouldn't be making a fuss.

00:05:58.249 --> 00:06:00.353
- No, it's okay!

00:06:00.387 --> 00:06:01.590
I'm happy.

00:06:01.623 --> 00:06:04.562
You don't know me,
but you stood up for me.

00:06:04.596 --> 00:06:06.533
Thank you very much!

00:06:06.567 --> 00:06:08.971
- I'm sorry I wasn't able
to help much.

00:06:10.708 --> 00:06:12.779
Wait, what happened
to that man?

00:06:12.812 --> 00:06:13.580
Where'd he go?

00:06:13.613 --> 00:06:16.052
- Oh, that was
a Mechanical Doll.

00:06:16.085 --> 00:06:17.956
- Mechanical Doll?

00:06:17.989 --> 00:06:20.561
- Yeah, and that guy
took it away with him.

00:06:20.594 --> 00:06:25.303
You see, he needed the key
in order to make the doll move.

00:06:25.336 --> 00:06:28.343
- So that's why
it was important.

00:06:28.376 --> 00:06:29.478
- Mm.

00:06:29.512 --> 00:06:32.218
- But why does he
want that doll?

00:06:32.251 --> 00:06:34.522
- Because it's very special.

00:06:34.555 --> 00:06:36.827
Not only can
that Mechanical Doll

00:06:36.860 --> 00:06:38.229
overpower a human,

00:06:38.263 --> 00:06:40.902
but it's capable
of 108 different moves.

00:06:40.935 --> 00:06:43.507
It's often used
for combat training.

00:06:43.540 --> 00:06:45.945
- So that's why.

00:06:45.978 --> 00:06:48.082
- But now it's--

00:06:48.116 --> 00:06:49.519
- [grunts]

00:06:49.553 --> 00:06:51.389
- [clang]
- [both gasp]

00:06:51.423 --> 00:06:52.792
- Wh--What was that?

00:06:52.825 --> 00:06:54.896
- Don't tell me he's already--

00:06:54.929 --> 00:06:55.998
This way!

00:06:56.032 --> 00:06:57.902
<i>[thrilling music]</i>

00:06:57.935 --> 00:07:04.949
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:07:07.087 --> 00:07:09.692
- Against a Hashira. Amazing.

00:07:09.726 --> 00:07:12.064
- Isn't it? It's the battle-type
Mechanical Doll

00:07:12.097 --> 00:07:13.734
built by my ancestors...

00:07:13.767 --> 00:07:16.372
the Yoriichi Type Zero.

00:07:16.406 --> 00:07:17.374
[swords clashing]

00:07:17.407 --> 00:07:20.079
- But why does he have six arms?

00:07:20.113 --> 00:07:21.517
- Oh, his arms?

00:07:21.550 --> 00:07:22.885
I asked the same thing.

00:07:22.919 --> 00:07:24.789
According to my father,
that Mechanical Doll

00:07:24.823 --> 00:07:27.294
was modeled
after an actual swordsman,

00:07:27.327 --> 00:07:28.663
and the only way
they could manage

00:07:28.697 --> 00:07:30.601
to replicate
the swordsman's moves

00:07:30.635 --> 00:07:33.106
was by giving it six arms.

00:07:33.139 --> 00:07:34.141
- [gasps]

00:07:35.243 --> 00:07:36.647
<i>That face...</i>

00:07:36.680 --> 00:07:39.519
<i>it seems familiar. But why?</i>

00:07:40.386 --> 00:07:43.125
About that swordsman,
who exactly was he?

00:07:43.159 --> 00:07:46.866
- Uh, sorry, but I don't
really know much about him.

00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:48.704
He was
from the Sengoku period.

00:07:48.737 --> 00:07:53.547
- S--Sengoku? You mean he lived
more than 300 years ago?

00:07:53.580 --> 00:07:55.083
- That's what I was told.

00:07:55.116 --> 00:07:58.890
- In all that time, it's never
broken down? Incredible.

00:07:58.924 --> 00:08:00.762
- The technology's so advanced.

00:08:00.795 --> 00:08:03.099
we're still
not able to catch up to it.

00:08:04.602 --> 00:08:07.842
So if it were to break,
there'd be no fixing it.

00:08:07.875 --> 00:08:08.877
- [gasps]

00:08:08.911 --> 00:08:11.082
- My father
suddenly passed away,

00:08:11.115 --> 00:08:12.718
and I have no siblings.

00:08:12.752 --> 00:08:15.624
I'm the only one
who can step up now.

00:08:15.658 --> 00:08:18.563
But I'm no good
with swords or dolls.

00:08:20.267 --> 00:08:22.238
- So that's why you--

00:08:22.271 --> 00:08:23.840
I think I get it now.

00:08:26.245 --> 00:08:28.550
Wow, he's incredible,

00:08:28.584 --> 00:08:31.222
even though
we're around the same age.

00:08:31.255 --> 00:08:33.794
He's talented and a Hashira.

00:08:33.827 --> 00:08:35.831
- Well, duh!
What did you expect?

00:08:35.865 --> 00:08:37.500
- Huh?
- I mean, he is a descendant

00:08:37.535 --> 00:08:39.539
of Sun Breathing users,
after all!

00:08:39.572 --> 00:08:42.210
That boy is a prodigy,
you know?

00:08:42.243 --> 00:08:44.950
He's in a different league
than the likes of you!

00:08:44.983 --> 00:08:46.687
[laughs]

00:08:46.720 --> 00:08:49.158
- Are you Tokito's crow?

00:08:49.191 --> 00:08:52.263
Wait, Sun Breathing?
The first Breathing Style?

00:08:53.265 --> 00:08:55.170
So he really is that amazing?

00:08:55.203 --> 00:08:56.205
- Hmm!

00:08:57.709 --> 00:09:00.881
- But that isn't Sun Breathing,
right?

00:09:00.914 --> 00:09:01.884
- Huh?!

00:09:01.917 --> 00:09:03.285
- [screams]

00:09:03.319 --> 00:09:04.622
- If you don't quit
your yapping,

00:09:04.655 --> 00:09:06.292
I'm gonna peck your eyes out!

00:09:06.325 --> 00:09:08.396
- Hey, now I remember!

00:09:08.429 --> 00:09:09.566
My dream!

00:09:09.599 --> 00:09:12.505
Yeah! I saw that man
in my dream!

00:09:12.538 --> 00:09:15.476
- Huh? Are you
an idiot or something?

00:09:15.511 --> 00:09:17.447
Isn't this
your first time here too?

00:09:17.480 --> 00:09:19.017
You sure know
how to make me laugh!

00:09:19.051 --> 00:09:19.920
I'll give you that!

00:09:19.953 --> 00:09:22.992
You met a warrior
from the Sengoku period?

00:09:23.026 --> 00:09:25.197
How old are you, exactly, huh?!

00:09:25.230 --> 00:09:26.633
- [muffled grunts]

00:09:26.666 --> 00:09:28.503
Listen, I'm sorry.

00:09:28.537 --> 00:09:30.875
I--I must be crazy.

00:09:30.908 --> 00:09:32.111
- No! No!

00:09:32.144 --> 00:09:35.718
I know!
Maybe it's an inherited memory?

00:09:35.751 --> 00:09:38.691
People talk about those a lot
in our village.

00:09:38.724 --> 00:09:40.426
It isn't
just your physical form

00:09:40.460 --> 00:09:41.730
that gets passed on.

00:09:41.763 --> 00:09:44.503
Living creatures
pass on their memories too.

00:09:44.536 --> 00:09:46.238
- Huh?

00:09:46.272 --> 00:09:47.975
- So what you saw in your dream

00:09:48.009 --> 00:09:50.681
had to have been
your ancestor's memories!

00:09:50.715 --> 00:09:53.987
- That's preposterous,
utterly preposterous!

00:09:54.789 --> 00:09:57.193
- How kind of you! Thank you!

00:09:57.227 --> 00:09:57.995
- [scoffs]

00:09:58.028 --> 00:10:00.668
- I'm Tanjiro. What's your name?

00:10:00.702 --> 00:10:02.772
- My name's Kotetsu.

00:10:02.806 --> 00:10:06.379
You can just do what I always do
and ignore the mean lady crow.

00:10:06.412 --> 00:10:07.380
[both yelp]

00:10:07.413 --> 00:10:08.683
- [clatter]
- [both gasp]

00:10:10.286 --> 00:10:11.589
- [gasps]

00:10:11.623 --> 00:10:14.194
[debris clatters]

00:10:14.228 --> 00:10:16.265
- Hey! His armor!

00:10:16.298 --> 00:10:19.004
- [shuddering]

00:10:20.306 --> 00:10:21.743
- [gasps] Kotetsu!

00:10:21.776 --> 00:10:23.647
<i>[wind blows]</i>

00:10:23.680 --> 00:10:25.082
<i>[sword slices]</i>

00:10:28.790 --> 00:10:30.661
<i>[wind blows]</i>

00:10:30.694 --> 00:10:32.030
<i>[sword slices]</i>

00:10:34.001 --> 00:10:35.938
- Kotetsu?

00:10:35.972 --> 00:10:37.073
- Kotetsu!

00:10:37.106 --> 00:10:38.844
I'll find you.

00:10:38.877 --> 00:10:40.379
I've got a good nose!

00:10:41.415 --> 00:10:43.854
Even if it's
a bit out of shape.

00:10:43.887 --> 00:10:46.225
I think he ran off this way.

00:10:46.258 --> 00:10:48.329
[sniffs]

00:10:48.362 --> 00:10:49.364
[sighs]

00:10:50.433 --> 00:10:51.736
Kotetsu!

00:10:51.769 --> 00:10:55.243
How in the world did you
manage to climb up that high?

00:10:56.613 --> 00:10:58.884
Come on,
you can't give up on your doll!

00:10:58.917 --> 00:11:01.188
I'll do anything I can
to help you out!

00:11:02.591 --> 00:11:03.994
What about your future?

00:11:04.696 --> 00:11:05.864
- Huh?

00:11:05.898 --> 00:11:09.271
- If you try hard now
for your future self,

00:11:09.305 --> 00:11:11.008
then a day will come

00:11:11.041 --> 00:11:14.949
where you can fight
and stand up for yourself!

00:11:15.751 --> 00:11:17.020
- No, it won't.

00:11:17.053 --> 00:11:20.360
I'm smart enough to know
that I'm a loser, okay?

00:11:20.393 --> 00:11:25.069
Because of me, it's all
gonna end with my generation!

00:11:25.102 --> 00:11:26.071
[gasps]

00:11:26.105 --> 00:11:27.341
Huh?

00:11:27.374 --> 00:11:28.510
Ouchy!

00:11:28.543 --> 00:11:31.314
- You cannot give up
and walk away from it.

00:11:31.348 --> 00:11:34.689
I really wish you wouldn't
talk about yourself that way.

00:11:34.722 --> 00:11:36.760
<i>- He didn't make a sound!</i>

00:11:36.793 --> 00:11:38.897
<i>Swordsmen are scary.</i>

00:11:38.931 --> 00:11:41.035
- Even if you can't do it,

00:11:41.068 --> 00:11:43.940
there will be someone
who will carry on for you.

00:11:43.974 --> 00:11:47.180
You have to do what you can
so it gets passed on.

00:11:47.213 --> 00:11:51.222
If you fail, maybe your kids
or grandkids will succeed.

00:11:51.255 --> 00:11:52.390
- [gasps]

00:11:52.424 --> 00:11:56.900
- I want to be the one to put
an end to Muzan Kibutsuji

00:11:56.933 --> 00:12:00.608
and to save my sister,
who's been turned into a demon.

00:12:00.641 --> 00:12:03.112
I might die
before I fulfill my goals...

00:12:03.145 --> 00:12:04.315
- [gasps]

00:12:04.348 --> 00:12:09.324
- but I have faith that someone
will carry out my wishes.

00:12:09.357 --> 00:12:13.098
The same way we were able to,
when we beat an Upper Rank.

00:12:13.967 --> 00:12:17.373
So I know in my heart
that someday

00:12:17.407 --> 00:12:20.113
Muzan Kibutsuji will fall.

00:12:20.146 --> 00:12:22.719
- [gasps]

00:12:22.752 --> 00:12:24.589
- Let's give our all!

00:12:24.623 --> 00:12:26.826
- [crying]

00:12:28.930 --> 00:12:32.805
I--I couldn't stand
to watch him break the doll.

00:12:32.839 --> 00:12:34.274
But that was before.

00:12:34.307 --> 00:12:38.048
The combat training
should last until nightfall.

00:12:38.082 --> 00:12:41.723
I promise I'll see this
through to the end.

00:12:41.756 --> 00:12:43.392
- Yeah!

00:12:44.763 --> 00:12:47.500
Really? So you're ten, Kotetsu?

00:12:47.534 --> 00:12:48.470
- Yeah.

00:12:48.504 --> 00:12:50.540
- My little brother is--

00:12:50.574 --> 00:12:52.679
- Huh?
- Huh?

00:12:52.712 --> 00:12:55.182
- What? You're already done?

00:12:56.318 --> 00:12:57.821
- I'm finished.

00:12:57.855 --> 00:12:59.525
It made for good training.

00:13:00.761 --> 00:13:01.963
Do I know you?

00:13:02.765 --> 00:13:04.368
Oh, that's right.

00:13:04.401 --> 00:13:06.305
My sword snapped, so...

00:13:06.338 --> 00:13:07.173
- [gasps]
- Huh?

00:13:07.206 --> 00:13:10.012
- ...this will do
for the time being.

00:13:10.814 --> 00:13:13.352
- [stammers]

00:13:13.386 --> 00:13:14.522
- Kotetsu!

00:13:14.555 --> 00:13:15.524
[winces]

00:13:15.557 --> 00:13:18.195
- There. Now dispose of it.

00:13:20.132 --> 00:13:22.639
<i>- Not even a whiff of malice.</i>

00:13:22.672 --> 00:13:25.376
<i>He must
not be doing it on purpose.</i>

00:13:25.410 --> 00:13:27.413
<i>That being said...</i>

00:13:29.217 --> 00:13:30.187
- Hmph!

00:13:30.220 --> 00:13:33.794
<i>- ...his crow is oozing
with animosity!</i>

00:13:33.827 --> 00:13:36.498
<i>She's so condescending.
What gives?</i>

00:13:37.534 --> 00:13:38.937
[gasps] Kotetsu!

00:13:38.970 --> 00:13:41.174
[thunder rumbling]

00:13:43.379 --> 00:13:44.348
[running footsteps]

00:13:44.381 --> 00:13:45.450
[panting]

00:13:45.483 --> 00:13:46.553
[gasps]

00:13:46.586 --> 00:13:48.557
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

00:13:48.590 --> 00:13:54.435
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:13:54.468 --> 00:13:56.438
[footsteps crunching]

00:13:57.842 --> 00:13:58.977
Kotetsu...

00:13:59.011 --> 00:14:02.618
let's make sure
and see if it still works.

00:14:02.652 --> 00:14:03.820
- [groans]

00:14:03.854 --> 00:14:05.423
- [grunts]

00:14:09.464 --> 00:14:11.468
[gears clicking]

00:14:15.878 --> 00:14:18.482
- Nothing. It must be...

00:14:20.888 --> 00:14:22.257
[both gasp]

00:14:22.290 --> 00:14:25.096
<i>[mellow music]</i>

00:14:26.699 --> 00:14:28.102
- All right!

00:14:28.135 --> 00:14:29.739
It's working, Kotetsu!

00:14:29.772 --> 00:14:31.174
That's... great.

00:14:33.714 --> 00:14:36.519
- Yes, it is, Mr. Tanjiro.

00:14:37.522 --> 00:14:38.957
And do you know why?

00:14:38.991 --> 00:14:40.628
Because now you can train
with this doll

00:14:40.661 --> 00:14:43.534
and become stronger than
that indifferent little jerk.

00:14:43.567 --> 00:14:46.806
And you'll have
my full support, no matter what!

00:14:46.840 --> 00:14:48.208
[thunder crashes]

00:14:48.242 --> 00:14:50.947
<i>- Huh? Wait, right now?</i>

00:14:53.820 --> 00:14:56.425
[shrieks]

00:14:56.458 --> 00:14:58.462
[shriek echoing]

00:15:00.834 --> 00:15:02.003
[gasps]

00:15:04.374 --> 00:15:06.445
Whoa!

00:15:06.478 --> 00:15:08.817
I'm gonna die!
Six arms is too many!

00:15:08.850 --> 00:15:10.688
- There are only five arms!

00:15:10.721 --> 00:15:12.525
Since that lousy jerk
broke one off,

00:15:12.558 --> 00:15:14.495
it's way easier to beat now.

00:15:14.529 --> 00:15:16.365
- [panting]

00:15:16.399 --> 00:15:19.171
- Mr. Tanjiro, please,
we need you stronger.

00:15:19.204 --> 00:15:21.943
so, next time we see him,
you can say,

00:15:21.976 --> 00:15:23.813
"That all you got, you scumbag?"

00:15:23.847 --> 00:15:25.016
- [winces]

00:15:25.049 --> 00:15:28.924
- "It's time to get a haircut,
seaweed head."

00:15:28.957 --> 00:15:31.729
"Pissant! You're ugly,
and your legs are short!"

00:15:31.763 --> 00:15:34.267
"Commit seppuku,
you shameless jerk!"

00:15:35.336 --> 00:15:38.610
- No! Mr. Kotetsu!
That's going too far!

00:15:38.643 --> 00:15:41.082
- You think we should
put his head on public display?

00:15:41.115 --> 00:15:43.553
- What? No!
I'm not saying any of that!

00:15:43.587 --> 00:15:44.889
- Yes, you are!

00:15:44.923 --> 00:15:47.393
- No!
- Please say it! Please?

00:15:47.427 --> 00:15:49.498
- [grunting]
- [running footsteps]

00:15:49.532 --> 00:15:50.534
[gasps]

00:15:53.540 --> 00:15:57.246
<i>Tokito was incredible.
He hardly broke a sweat...</i>

00:15:58.282 --> 00:16:01.488
<i>despite being smaller
and younger than me.</i>

00:16:02.490 --> 00:16:04.094
<i>I have to train harder</i>

00:16:04.127 --> 00:16:06.766
<i>so that I can become stronger!</i>

00:16:09.337 --> 00:16:10.339
[gags]

00:16:11.910 --> 00:16:15.049
[groaning]

00:16:16.686 --> 00:16:18.122
- Come on, Mr. Tanjiro!

00:16:18.156 --> 00:16:20.459
Don't tell me that's all
it takes to kill you.

00:16:20.493 --> 00:16:21.662
Now come on! Get up!

00:16:21.696 --> 00:16:22.932
I'm gonna say it
one more time.

00:16:22.965 --> 00:16:23.934
Look at me!

00:16:23.967 --> 00:16:25.670
- [groaning]

00:16:27.040 --> 00:16:28.075
- All you're doing now

00:16:28.108 --> 00:16:30.379
is moving out of habit,
Mr. Tanjiro!

00:16:31.615 --> 00:16:35.289
You're not reacting off your
opponent's moves whatsoever.

00:16:35.323 --> 00:16:38.062
That's why you're getting beat!
Understand?

00:16:38.095 --> 00:16:40.333
Which, in other words,
means you don't even have

00:16:40.366 --> 00:16:43.072
the fundamentals
of sword fighting down yet.

00:16:43.105 --> 00:16:45.176
It's a miracle you haven't died!

00:16:45.209 --> 00:16:47.548
Good thing I'm here
to expose your weak points

00:16:47.581 --> 00:16:48.883
until we fix them!

00:16:48.917 --> 00:16:51.088
And to give you
some extra motivation,

00:16:51.121 --> 00:16:53.458
no food until we're finished!

00:16:54.796 --> 00:16:56.097
- Right.

00:16:56.900 --> 00:16:58.335
[groans]

00:16:59.204 --> 00:17:01.041
- Faster, Mr. Tanjiro!

00:17:01.074 --> 00:17:02.377
You gotta pick up the pace!

00:17:02.410 --> 00:17:04.982
If that doll wasn't armed
with practice sticks,

00:17:05.015 --> 00:17:06.051
you'd be dead!

00:17:06.084 --> 00:17:07.286
Get it together!

00:17:07.320 --> 00:17:10.125
We're on day five now,
so starting tomorrow,

00:17:10.159 --> 00:17:12.932
I'm gonna arm the doll
with swords!

00:17:12.965 --> 00:17:15.671
- That is, if I even live
to see day six!

00:17:15.705 --> 00:17:17.708
I'm--I'm gonna die!

00:17:19.410 --> 00:17:21.883
- No food for you today, either!

00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:23.486
<i>- [whimpers]</i>

00:17:23.520 --> 00:17:26.091
<i>Mr. Kotetsu's
surprisingly analytical.</i>

00:17:26.124 --> 00:17:29.364
<i>But as a swordsmanship
instructor, he was terrible!</i>

00:17:29.398 --> 00:17:31.368
<i>- It's like he has no idea...</i>
- Just a second!

00:17:31.401 --> 00:17:33.206
<i>- what the limits
of the human body are,</i>

00:17:33.239 --> 00:17:35.944
<i>and his brutal training
reflects that.</i>

00:17:35.977 --> 00:17:37.514
<i>He's gotten to be so ruthless,</i>

00:17:37.548 --> 00:17:41.321
<i>that he'll withhold food
and water if you fall short.</i>

00:17:41.354 --> 00:17:43.694
<i>But a human
can only go without water</i>

00:17:43.727 --> 00:17:45.129
<i>for three days or so.</i>

00:17:47.366 --> 00:17:48.536
- Hmph!

00:17:48.570 --> 00:17:53.145
<i>- It's pure tyranny
born out of his ignorance.</i>

00:17:56.586 --> 00:17:59.892
<i>[Tanjiro] Luckily, I was able
to survive, thanks to rainfall.</i>

00:17:59.925 --> 00:18:01.596
[wails]

00:18:01.630 --> 00:18:04.502
<i>All throughout
these harsh training sessions,</i>

00:18:04.535 --> 00:18:08.810
<i>I went without water,
without food, without sleep.</i>

00:18:10.581 --> 00:18:12.618
[groans]

00:18:12.652 --> 00:18:17.426
<i>And then I started to cross
the River to the Afterlife.</i>

00:18:18.228 --> 00:18:20.199
<i>I was walking across a bridge,</i>

00:18:20.232 --> 00:18:22.571
<i>feeling an indescribable bliss.</i>

00:18:22.604 --> 00:18:27.346
<i>Only to get dizzy from hunger
and fall in the river.</i>

00:18:28.148 --> 00:18:29.953
<i>The water got darker and darker,</i>

00:18:29.986 --> 00:18:32.457
<i>heavier and heavier...</i>

00:18:32.490 --> 00:18:34.160
<i>until I felt a strange warmth.</i>

00:18:34.193 --> 00:18:37.601
<i>It was almost
like I was being massaged.</i>

00:18:38.469 --> 00:18:41.108
<i>When I glanced
towards the bottom of the river,</i>

00:18:41.141 --> 00:18:42.578
<i>I saw something shiny,</i>

00:18:42.612 --> 00:18:45.617
<i>so I swam towards it
while being massaged.</i>

00:18:46.819 --> 00:18:50.059
<i>Oddly enough,
despite being underwater,</i>

00:18:50.092 --> 00:18:52.764
<i>I could smell
the shimmering stone.</i>

00:18:55.704 --> 00:18:56.740
[gasps]

00:18:56.773 --> 00:18:59.746
<i>What is this? This smell?</i>

00:18:59.779 --> 00:19:02.316
<i>It's different
than the Opening Thread.</i>

00:19:03.587 --> 00:19:04.354
<i>[gasps]</i>

00:19:04.387 --> 00:19:06.125
<i>Left side of the head!</i>

00:19:06.158 --> 00:19:07.761
<i>Neck.</i>

00:19:07.794 --> 00:19:09.097
<i>Right side.</i>

00:19:09.130 --> 00:19:10.634
<i>Left side!</i>

00:19:10.667 --> 00:19:12.170
<i>Right thigh.</i>

00:19:12.203 --> 00:19:13.272
<i>Right shoulder!</i>

00:19:13.305 --> 00:19:15.744
<i>[gasps] Now!</i>

00:19:22.123 --> 00:19:23.459
[groans]

00:19:23.492 --> 00:19:26.700
- There you go!
You finally got one strike in!

00:19:26.733 --> 00:19:27.668
Though it was so weak,

00:19:27.701 --> 00:19:29.571
I don't think the doll
even flinched!

00:19:29.605 --> 00:19:32.076
Congrats! You earned some food!

00:19:32.109 --> 00:19:33.245
- [gasps]

00:19:33.278 --> 00:19:34.982
Rice balls and pickled plums!

00:19:35.016 --> 00:19:37.621
And I want
high-quality gyokuro tea!

00:19:40.226 --> 00:19:41.930
[grunting]

00:19:41.963 --> 00:19:45.737
Tasty!

00:19:48.910 --> 00:19:50.413
<i>Good. Good!</i>

00:19:50.446 --> 00:19:52.183
<i>His moves, I see them!</i>

00:19:52.217 --> 00:19:54.655
<i>I see them
much better than before,</i>

00:19:54.688 --> 00:19:57.460
<i>and I've got
my stamina back now!</i>

00:20:00.466 --> 00:20:04.474
<i>Somehow, I can tell by the scent
where he's going to strike!</i>

00:20:05.276 --> 00:20:08.349
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:20:08.382 --> 00:20:10.386
<i>Even better,
I can pick up the scent</i>

00:20:10.419 --> 00:20:12.791
<i>faster than the Opening Thread.</i>

00:20:13.827 --> 00:20:17.366
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:19.003
<i>Yes! I can do it!</i>

00:20:19.036 --> 00:20:21.609
<i>I can land a full-strength blow!</i>

00:20:21.642 --> 00:20:23.012
[gasps]

00:20:23.045 --> 00:20:24.948
<i>But what if it breaks?</i>

00:20:27.420 --> 00:20:29.124
- Do it!
- [gasps]

00:20:29.157 --> 00:20:31.128
- If it does break...

00:20:31.161 --> 00:20:34.134
then I--then I'll just fix it!

00:20:34.167 --> 00:20:35.904
- [gasps]

00:20:37.006 --> 00:20:39.377
<i>- Mr. Tanjiro,
you're far too kind.</i>

00:20:39.410 --> 00:20:41.816
<i>But there's no time to hesitate.</i>

00:20:42.818 --> 00:20:44.086
<i>If you do,</i>

00:20:44.120 --> 00:20:46.025
<i>it's sure
to cost you your life!</i>

00:20:46.058 --> 00:20:47.594
<i>And I don't want that!</i>

00:20:47.628 --> 00:20:51.836
<i>What I want is for you
to be the strongest!</i>

00:20:56.979 --> 00:20:57.981
- That hurt!

00:20:58.014 --> 00:21:00.987
- Mr. Tanjiro!
Are you all right?

00:21:01.020 --> 00:21:02.323
- Ow, ow, ow.

00:21:02.357 --> 00:21:06.397
S--Sorry. I broke
the sword that you lent me.

00:21:06.431 --> 00:21:08.603
- Don't worry about that.
It's okay.

00:21:11.609 --> 00:21:13.245
Huh? Hey!

00:21:13.278 --> 00:21:16.853
<i>[ominous music]</i>

00:21:16.886 --> 00:21:18.221
- Something came out!

00:21:18.255 --> 00:21:20.092
K--K--Kotetsu!
Something came out!

00:21:20.125 --> 00:21:21.361
What is that?!

00:21:21.394 --> 00:21:23.900
- Don't ask me!
It's not like I put it in there!

00:21:29.310 --> 00:21:31.081
<i>[singers vocalizing]</i>

00:21:31.114 --> 00:21:32.116
- [gasps]

00:21:32.149 --> 00:21:33.653
- What could that possibly be?

00:21:33.686 --> 00:21:34.688
It's a sword.

00:21:34.722 --> 00:21:38.461
But it's gotta be
at least 300 years old, right?

00:21:40.600 --> 00:21:41.602
- [gasps]

00:21:42.905 --> 00:21:44.876
<i>["Koi Kogare" playing]</i>

00:21:44.909 --> 00:21:51.922
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:12.984 --> 00:23:14.420
[page rustles]

00:23:14.453 --> 00:23:16.391
- It really suits you, Nezuko!

00:23:16.424 --> 00:23:17.928
- Mmm!

00:23:17.961 --> 00:23:19.999
[humming a tune]

00:23:20.032 --> 00:23:21.235
- You like it, don't you?

00:23:21.268 --> 00:23:22.504
- Mmm!

00:23:22.538 --> 00:23:25.644
- Now it's time
for a Taisho-era secret!

00:23:25.677 --> 00:23:27.881
It's actually about Kotetsu.

00:23:27.915 --> 00:23:29.785
They say his face
is such a dead ringer

00:23:29.818 --> 00:23:32.323
for the mask he wears,
that in all honesty

00:23:32.357 --> 00:23:34.562
he probably doesn't need
to wear a mask at all.

00:23:34.595 --> 00:23:36.364
I wonder if it's true.

00:23:36.398 --> 00:23:38.035
- [grumbling]
- He might be merciless

00:23:38.068 --> 00:23:39.170
when it comes to his training,

00:23:39.204 --> 00:23:41.976
but I know that deep down,
he's a sweet kid at heart!

00:23:42.009 --> 00:23:42.978
- [chuckles]

00:23:43.011 --> 00:23:44.548
- Next, Episode 3,

00:23:44.581 --> 00:23:46.986
"A Sword From Over
Three Hundred Years Ago!"

00:23:47.019 --> 00:23:48.288
I'm hot!

00:23:48.321 --> 00:23:49.558
- Mr. Tanjiro!

00:23:49.591 --> 00:23:51.294
- Where'd you run off to?
- [gasps]

00:23:51.327 --> 00:23:53.566
- We have to train again!

00:23:53.600 --> 00:23:55.436
If you slack off
after one good day,

00:23:55.469 --> 00:23:56.773
you'll be back
where you started!

00:23:56.806 --> 00:24:00.279
Remember, "Persistence
prevails when all else fails!"

00:24:00.312 --> 00:24:02.383
"Slow and steady wins the race!"

00:24:02.416 --> 00:24:03.652
Mr. Tanjiro, where are you?

00:24:03.686 --> 00:24:05.322
- Nezuko, let's go!
- Mr. Tanjiro,

00:24:05.355 --> 00:24:06.825
- where are you hiding, huh?!
- Mmm!

